They don't pay taxes on pay cheques if they work for a company that is registered on reserve. There is no property tax on reserve because you cannot own or hold title to land on reserve as it is a ward of the federation same with the people too, that's why they deal with the feds and not provincial governments. They are given a per capita distribution which basically covers the costs of their health centers, band offices (local government) and some of their social programs as well as infrastructure. That money gets allocated by the government in power, some of these people will never see a dime. Some reserves got lucky with the placement of their quarantined lands as they have had potential for business opportunities...some aren't lucky because they live in swamp in the middle of no where.
Hard to be well rounded when 80 percent of the province is ignorantly lobsided. Never the less, the world keeps on turning.
